post_text:
Back to School Night for remote instruction is Monday, August 17th. The Texas Education Agency has made a number of changes to home learning and we want to be sure you know what your responsibilities are.

We will have 2 sessions where you will sit down and learn how to access your child’s learning materials and turn in work. The first session will begin at 6:30 and the second session will begin at 7:00.

Please have the person who will be responsible for your child’s learning attend the session with your child. Please have all other family members stay home so that we can practice social distancing. If possible, bring the device your child will work on with you. If you need a device from the school, please call 512-856-2422 or email jlarson@couplandisd.org before Monday at noon so we can have the equipment ready for check out.

If you are unable to attend, please contact your child’s teacher to schedule an appointment because your child will not be able to start remote learning without his/her log-in information and instructional materials.

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Coupland ISD is accepting applications for a full time Cafeteria Manager. The ideal candidate has experience in planning, preparing and serving meals. View the job descripton here. https://drive.google.com/file/d/0Bxz0flVEI1jXNjAzeXZtbTViTkE/view?usp=sharing

185 days following the school calendar (august - May)

Coupland ISD provides benefits that include: 10 paid personal days per year, health insurance with employer contribution of $385, $10,000 life insurance policy, free before/after care for school age children.

Interested applicants should submit the application for support personnel and a copy of the Certified Food Manager certificate to Tammy Brinkman at tbrinkman@couplandisd.org

post_text: We miss our students, and hope you are all well. The most important thing you can do right now is stay at home! If that’s not possible, practice social distancing by staying 6 feet from others. Wash your hands with soap and water for 20 seconds and disinfect frequently touched surfaces such as doorknobs and countertops. Avoid touching your eyes, nose, or mouth, and cover a cough or sneeze with your elbow. If you have symptoms of COVID-19 – a fever, dry cough, or shortness of breath, call your doctor. Remember, by staying apart now, we can all be together again faster!

Texas parents can now visit the TXSchools.gov MealFinder Map to find locations near them where local school systems are offering free school meals—both breakfast and lunch—for pick-up while school buildings are closed because of the novel coronavirus (COVID-19). Launched by the Texas Education Agency (TEA), in partnership with the Office of the Governor and Texas Department of Agriculture (TDA), the TXSchools.gov MealFinder Map is designed to help parents and students easily find school meals during the unprecedented disruption to schools caused by COVID-19.

Once parents go to the site, they click “Meal Pick-Up Locations” to bring up a map of locations. Parents can type their address, and the map will zoom into meal pick-up locations that are up and running near them.

post_text:
A message from the Superintendent:

The safety and health of our students are the utmost concern to me and the Coupland Board of Trustees. There has been a great deal of information about the Corona virus in the news over the last few weeks and I have participated in discussions with the Texas Education Agency, Region 13 Austin area superintendents and the Williamson County Emergency Operations team. As a result of these discussions, the East Williamson County superintendents have decided to cancel classes through March 20th. All extracurricular activities have been suspended until further notice.

post_text:
Barn Hill Preserve will be visiting Coupland on Friday, November 1st.
Permission Slips to for this program are being sent home today.
Each student will need to turn in a permission slip in order to participate.
Barn Hill Preserve's FREE mobile program consists of one, 45-minute oral presentation on our LIVE animal ambassadors. This program offers students the unique experience to get up close and personal with animals they may have never seen before! Students participate by asking questions, getting involved in demonstrations, and responding to the speaker, making our program both educational and entertaining!

Barn Hill Preserve's exotic animal education program is 100% FREE to both your students and school. We fund our free program by providing students the opportunity to purchase pictures with our live animal ambassadors. These 6x4 photos are $10 each and are taken on our jungle themed backdrop!

post_text:
GT Nominations
Nominations of students in grades K and up are currently being accepted for screening for inclusion in the Gifted and Talented (G/T) program. The Gifted and Talented program is designed to meet the needs of traditionally defined gifted students. Students selected for the G/T program demonstrate above average ability, task commitment, and creativity. The district criteria for screening for the Gifted and Talented program is based on:

• Parent or teacher nomination
• National achievement test (SAGES-2)
• Cognitive Abilities Test (SAGES-2 Reasoning)
• Parent rating scale and questionnaire
• Teacher rating scale (by Joseph Renzulli and Robert K. Hartman)

If your child has already been identified as part of the Gifted and Talented program, he/she will not need further screening.
If you wish for your child to be considered for the Gifted and Talented program, you may pick up a nomination form in the office or one is available on our website.
text:
GT Nominations
Nominations of students in grades K and up are currently being accepted for screening for inclusion in the Gifted and Talented (G/T) program. The Gifted and Talented program is designed to meet the needs of traditionally defined gifted students. Students selected for the G/T program demonstrate above average ability, task commitment, and creativity. The district criteria for screening for the Gifted and Talented program is based on:

• Parent or teacher nomination
• National achievement test (SAGES-2)
• Cognitive Abilities Test (SAGES-2 Reasoning)
• Parent rating scale and questionnaire
• Teacher rating scale (by Joseph Renzulli and Robert K. Hartman)

If your child has already been identified as part of the Gifted and Talented program, he/she will not need further screening.
If you wish for your child to be considered for the Gifted and Talented program, you may pick up a nomination form in the office or one is available on our website.

We made it through our first three days of school! It was great to see all of our returning students and also all of our new kiddos!

Just a few reminders.....
Morning drop off begins at 7:20 am. For their safety, students are not allowed to be dropped off to wait in front of the school prior to that time. Before school care is available starting at 6:50 am in the library (fees apply).

All students should report to the gym and will be released to their classes by the morning attendant. Instructional time starts at 7:45am. Please drop off by 7:40 am so that they are on time.

After school pick up is 3:15 pm -3:30 pm. Please make sure to pick up no later than 3:30.

We are looking forward to another wonderful year at CISD!!

Barn Hill Preserve
January 20, 2018 at 9:22 AM ·

Do you want to win a free trip to Barn Hill Preserve? We are excited to announce a brand new animal ambassador coming to Barn Hill! The first person to guess the species of animal correctly wins a free encounter tour to Barn Hill Preserve!

Here are a few hints:
- I am the only living member in my Order
- I closely resemble (though am not related to) an animal in South America. I have also been described as resembling a common domestic animal
- I am primarily nocturnal
- My prey is sometimes feared for its ferocious appetite and constant search for food

Post your guess in the comments below. We will announce the winner and animal next week!

post_text:
Barnhill Preserve will be visiting Coupland ISD on
Monday, 2/12 @ 8:30 am.

Order forms for pictures were sent home on Thursday.

Parents are welcome to attend.

They will be bringing a baby sloth, blue tongued skink and a bearded dragon.

This is a free program that is funded by providing students with the opportunity to take photos with the animal ambassadors for $10 each. Cash or check payable to Barn Hill Preserve - Please have exact change.
(Based on behavior and well being on the day of event, photo ambassadors are subject to change).

This is a wonderful program and we are delighted that they decided to come visit Coupland ISD again!

Our One Act Play competition will be held tomorrow, Wednesday, December 13th at the Mary Alice Marshall Performing Arts Center at Temple College.

Please make sure permission slips and lunch money has been turned in no later than today.

Students will be transported by school bus.

They will leave campus by 8:15 am. Rehearsal is at 11:00 (parents are not permitted to attend rehearsal time), and their performance is at 2:00 pm.

Everyone is invited to attend the performance.

Awards and critiques will be after the final performance at approximately 5:00 pm.

Estimated arrival time to Coupland is approximately 8:30 - 9:30 PM.

The OAP Director has requested that students ride the bus to and from the performance. We ask that everyone be prompt in picking up your student from school.

2487 S. 5th Street
Temple, TX 76504

Also, a big thank you to all of the Grandparents that donated this morning.
J. Larson

We made it through our first day of school! It was great to see all of our returning students and also all of our new kiddos!

Just a few reminders.....
Morning drop off begins at 7:20 am. Students are not allowed to be dropped off to wait in front of the school prior to that time. Before school care is available starting at 7 am in the library (fees apply).

All students should report to the gym and will be released to their classes at 7:40 am.

After school pick up is 3:15 pm -3:30 pm. Please make sure to pick up no later than 3:30.

We are looking forward to a wonderful year at CISD!!

post_text:
Harvest Fest is fast approaching!!!
Every classroom has a themed basket that will be featured in our live auction!
Students are asked to contribute items for their class basket.

Every bit helps!

The themes for each basket is below. If you cannot purchase items for the basket, but would like to contribute monetarily - you may send your contribution to the teacher and they can purchase items to put towards the basket.

Kindergarten - Fall/Autumn
1st Grade - Outdoor Fun
2nd Grade - Movie Night
3rd Grade - Reading
4th Grade - University of Texas
5th Grade - Gift Wrap
6th Grade - Texas A & M
7th Grade - State of Texas (Red/white/Blue)
8th Grade - Disney

Thank you Parents, Family, Friends and all who are helping make this the best Harvest Fest yet!!
